abstracts.cdata!:
The project would include: (i) the
            development by corporation of seven ranches of 12,000 ha
            each, which would develop systems of livestock production
            and mixed farming, through field trials, which would
            stimulate increased livestock production in the outer
            islands; (ii) a small pilot program of credit to medium
            income private farmers located in the project areas, who
            would utilize the knowledge developed on the government
            ranches; and (iii) technical assistance for on-ranch
            training abroad of corporation executive personnel and
            preparation of another livestock project.
